			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3764246">
									

<p>I spent a good 60% of this document reading the guy's name as 'dabo', and felt really odd and confused when I reread it and my brain had to correct itself. Weird.</p>
<p>Anyway, this was funny to read my first time going through it, but kind of bugged me in a couple places once I reread it, mostly having to do with the email exchange between <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">dabo</span> dado and that client. I don't know, it's just kind of hard for me to buy that the guy took a pill, started sending emails (while in the process of going through the myriad of symptoms that imbibers suffer from as they get older and hornier), and then flipped the switch from WTF? to DTF? while typing.</p>
<p>Maybe it's just me, and I'm looking at it/envisioning it the wrong way or something, but it just read really weirdly to me.</p>
<p>In general, though, I do like this. Even though I'm probably not the hugest fan of the idea itself, the comical way it was presented did really get me, so I'll +1.</p>

